
# 0.8.0
- Removed the `java`/Picard MarkDuplicates dependency entirely; duplicate
  removal now runs through `bam-dedup` (pure Python/Cython, pysam-based).
  `mgatk/bin/picard.jar` (~15MB) is gone from the repo.
- **Breaking**: `--max-javamem`/`-jm` is deprecated and does nothing (there's
  no JVM left to size). It's still accepted so existing scripts don't fail;
  passing it now prints a one-line notice instead.
- Fixed a latent bug in `tenx` mode: duplicate marking is barcode-aware (so
  reads from different cells at the same position are never collapsed), but
  the previous mechanism (Picard's `BARCODE_TAG`) turned out to do UMI-aware
  matching that silently found zero duplicates whenever no true per-molecule
  UMI was supplied (no `-ub` flag) -- the common case for standard
  scATAC-seq/mtscATAC-seq data. `bam-dedup`'s barcode-aware grouping fixes
  this and matches Picard's behavior in the cases where it did work correctly.
- Refactored the standalone scripts under `mgatk/bin/python/` (invoked via
  `os.system('python script.py ...')`) into a proper importable package,
  `mgatk.processing`, called directly from the CLI and Snakemake rules.
  Hardened the remaining external-process calls (snakemake, Rscript,
  cellbender) to check for failure instead of silently ignoring it.
- Modernized dependencies for current Python/snakemake/pysam/numpy/pandas;
  fixed several Python-2-only and deprecated-API bugs along the way.
- Replaced the placeholder test suite (a single test with no assertions)
  with real unit and end-to-end coverage; refreshed `tests/README.md` and
  the GitHub issue templates.

